docs.lead_paragraph: A Distinction Too Nice for Most Professor IRVING FISHER'S disclosure in an Ohio Methodist church of a conversation which he had with the late President HARDING shortly after the latter was nominated in 1920 is justified by him on the ground that the talk was "personal" but not "confidential."
